about.description:
This package is a generic way to obtain binutils for your system
that conda-forge used to compile its ecosystem.  This compiler is,
therefore, guaranteed to be ABI compatible with the conda packages
you have installed.

This compiler metapackage is a convenience ONLY for users.
Do NOT use this package as a build or host dependency in other
recipes.

name: binutils-meta
raw_recipe:
# This file created by conda-build 3.18.9
# ------------------------------------------------

package:
    name: binutils-meta
    version: 1.0.4
build:
    number: 0
    string: '0'
requirements:
    host:
        - binutils_impl_linux-ppc64le 2.28.1 h04c84fa_2
        - binutils_linux-ppc64le 7.2.0 h14882df_25
    run:
        - binutils_linux-ppc64le
test:
    commands:
        - $LD --help
        - ar --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking ar resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which ar) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - as --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking as resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which as) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - ld --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking ld resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which ld) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - nm --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking nm resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which nm) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - size --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking size resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which size) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - strings --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking strings resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which strings) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - strip --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking strip resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which strip) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - addr2line --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking addr2line resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which addr2line) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - c++filt --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking c++filt resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which c++filt) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - elfedit --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking elfedit resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which elfedit) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - gprof --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking gprof resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which gprof) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - ld.bfd --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking ld.bfd resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which ld.bfd) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - objcopy --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking objcopy resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which objcopy) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - objdump --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking objdump resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which objdump) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - ranlib --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking ranlib resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which ranlib) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
        - readelf --help > /dev/null
        - echo "Checking readelf resolves to a path containing ${BUILD}"
        - readlink $(which readelf) | grep -q "${BUILD}"
about:
    description: 'This package is a generic way to obtain binutils for your system

        that conda-forge used to compile its ecosystem.  This compiler is,

        therefore, guaranteed to be ABI compatible with the conda packages

        you have installed.


        This compiler metapackage is a convenience ONLY for users.

        Do NOT use this package as a build or host dependency in other

        recipes.

        '
    home: https://conda-forge.org
    license: BSD
    summary: A metapackage to obtain binutils
extra:
    copy_test_source_files: true
    final: true
    recipe-maintainers:
        - chrisburr
        - duncanmmacleod
        - scopatz
